HEADWORD: casebook
<hw>case"book`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a book in which detailed written
records of cases are kept and which are a source of information for
subsequent work. Such books are often used as supplements to texts in
law schools.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

